x4freetext: Measurement of activation resonance integrals at
infinite dilution with a Ge-Li gamma-ray spectrometer
Central reflector and thermal column of reactor RA-1.
Solutions containing the same proportions of unknown
Ratios of reduced capture integral to the thermal
capture cross section were measured using the cadmium
ratio technique or the two spectra method.
Values of reduced resonance integrals relative to ther-
mal cross section determined relative to gold,for which
Ratio of resonance integral to thermal sigma =15.69
Experimental results were corrected for neutron
epithermal self-shielding and for deviation from a 1/E
